Program: Discovery
Title: Scott's Legacy: Programme 3 - Mars
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00qz8bn
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 6 May 2012
One hundred years ago, the first humans reached the South Pole of this planet. More than 40 years ago, man first walked on the moon. When will our species first set foot to explore the planet Mars? Kevin Fong seeks a likely launch date, and asks who will get us there and why we really need to explore the Red Planet. Show less